
This file includes examples of using MOTOR.

Main Function Summary 

Specific functions ...
(queens N ..... )  run either confused or N-queens. See queens.lisp
(queens-variables N)  creates initial problem structure for queens or confused queens.

(mpr .... )        run model pattern recognizer. See mpr-simple.lisp, mpr-setup.lisp
(mpr-variables)    creates initial problem structure for mpr.

Problem-specific functions ...
(consistent-p Sym1 Var1 Sym2 Var2 ...) determines whether arc constraints in problem
					allow this assignment pair or not. 
(arc-p  Sym1 Sym2) determines whether an arc exists in problem between these symbols

Generic functions ...
(show-solution)    repeats output of either queens or mpr function with more detail.

